With the Mirror Flats survey complete, the cartographic record must now extend through the Glasswind Belt and down to the Tidemouth Dunes. Glass scorpion matriarchs have established new breeding positions that block standard observation paths, glassworm tunnel sentinels have sealed off burrowing access to subsurface survey markers, and tidemouth crab broodmothers are disrupting the coastal waypoint installations. Clear one of each to complete the full-route survey.
The full Reach survey from the Mirror Flats to the Tidemouth Dunes is now on record. Glassworm tunnel access has been restored, scorpion territory boundaries are documented, and the coastal waypoint installations are back in service. The updated cartographic packet has been dispatched to the Kowloon Jade Clerk commission that funded the survey.

